-- Chiefs Player Shoots Himself Near Football Stadium, Police Say
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-12-01T16:37:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-01/chiefs-player-shoots-himself-near-football-stadium-police-say.html
A  Kansas City  Chiefs player shot
himself this morning near Arrowhead Stadium, Kansas City Police
Chief Darryl Forte said on Twitter.  The unidentified player shot and killed his girlfriend,
then drove to the National Football League team’s practice
center near Arrowhead Stadium where he shot and killed himself,
Kansas City, Missouri, television station KCTV said on its
website.  “We can confirm that there was an incident at Arrowhead
earlier this morning,” the Chiefs said in a statement. ’’We are
cooperating with authorities in their investigation.’’  Messages left for the Kansas City Police Department’s Media
Unit and NFL spokesman  Brian McCarthy  weren’t immediately
returned.  The Chiefs are scheduled to host the Carolina Panthers
tomorrow. The Panthers are still planning to travel to Kansas
City, the team said on Twitter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Bensch in London at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 